import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  

export default class MDXContent extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props)
    this.layout = null
  }
  render() {
    const { components, ...props } = this.props

    return <MDXTag
             name="wrapper"
             
             components={components}><MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"empirical-costs"}}>{`Empirical Costs`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`While this information is essentially confidential, these are numbers and impressions of apps and websites that I have previously built before for companies between taking over start up apps to working for large scale companies through a digital agency.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`The "too long; didn't read" summary for all of this is that you basically get what you pay for, although there are cavenats based `}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"digital-agencies-in-australia"}}>{`Digital Agencies in Australia`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h3" components={components} props={{"id":"employee--charge-rates-through-the-agencies"}}>{`Employee + Charge Rates Through The Agencies`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Digital agencies I've worked with quote clients with costs that look like the following:`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="table" components={components}>
<MDXTag name="thead" components={components} parentName="table">
<MDXTag name="tr" components={components} parentName="thead">
<MDXTag name="th" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`Role`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="th" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`Company Hourly Charge (includes employee wage)`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="th" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`Employee Wage`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="tbody" components={components} parentName="table">
<MDXTag name="tr" components={components} parentName="tbody">
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`Junior Developer`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`\$150`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`\$50/hr`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="tr" components={components} parentName="tbody">
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`Senior Developer`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`\$225`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`\$75-120/hr`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="tr" components={components} parentName="tbody">
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`Junior Designer`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`\$125`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`\$30-50/hr`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="tr" components={components} parentName="tbody">
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`Senior Designer`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`\$175`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`\$75-100/hr`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="tr" components={components} parentName="tbody">
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`Senior UX`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`\$225`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="td" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`\$70-100/hr`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`The figures above should give some insight to what you could be looking to pay if you employ a company digital team.`}</MDXTag>

<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`The work I've built through digital agencies are massive companies that in themselves are slow because of the size of the company, but for the sake of information about what they normally pay the agency then here is a short list of what they've charged for work:`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="table" components={components}>
<MDXTag name="thead" components={components} parentName="table">
<MDXTag name="tr" components={components} parentName="thead">
<MDXTag name="th" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`Company + Product`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="th" components={components} parentName="tr" props={{"align":null}}>{`Cost`}</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="tbody" components={components} parentName="table">
<MDXTag name="tr" components={components} parentName="tbody">

</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="tr" components={components} parentName="tbody">

<MDXTag name="tr" components={components} parentName="tbody">

<MDXTag name="tr" components={components} parentName="tbody">

<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`It is worth noting that these companies themselves work slow (book a shitload of meeting and burn time) or are Government so they drive costs up themselves by requiring more employee time, but that should at least give you some idea between what some companies pay the "better" Australian digital agencies.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Complexity varies for the projects in the above applications too.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"outsourced-companies"}}>{`Outsourced Companies`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`This critique is more something from personal experience with companies like Appster. A few startups who had their development done through Appster ended up with them outsourcing a lot to India for their profit margin.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`Example bad case that happened with NightGuru that I saw was that they were quoted for an iOS only app at \$70,000 which would take three months but that blew out to eighteen months before they launched the product.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`They took cuts for the sake of ongoing costs for the company but that meant their MySQL database was not fault tolerant, the app itself was not fault tolerate and there were no tests or documentation for the end product code they were given.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"outsourced-products"}}>{`Outsourced Products`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`The cheapest but by far worst quality. You can "possibly" get away with a cheap MVP using this method to test the waters, but be warned that if you think the product has potential then not only will you likely need to upgrade the entire app/website setup for a version two major iteration but also migrate all entire databases onto more feasible schemas. `}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`These guys are generally uni students/juniors who have not had much experience on enterprise work. A case with Fef recently was that he decided to outsource to a freelancer for \\$5000 on his jewellary store app but that took six months and he ended up throwing it out and paying \\$20,000 for a company in Brisbane to do the job which Tom says they promised in 12 weeks which started development back in March but still isn't fully completed.`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"personal-product"}}>{`Personal Product`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`The entire selling point behind my company is to sell and win the client back time. The products are robust, highly accessible and the level of documentation, testing and fault tolerance that the client wants will increase or reduce time/costs. `}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`This puts focus back on the actual results startups and clients are trying to get to which is actually getting the product in user hands and pushing their brand and business, while also allowing the flexibility for products of variable complexity to be adhered to.`}</MDXTag>
